11/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Dragan Sutanovic, the chairman of the Serbian Parliament's security committee, said on Saturday (9 August) that US security services are willing to co-operate with their Serbian counterparts in the global fight against terrorism. Sutanovic is just back from a trip to the United States, where he met with officials from the FBI, the CIA, the National Security Agency, the defence department and the New York City Police. He said that US officials pledged to provide expertise and open offices in Belgrade soon.
In other news, a delegation of US congressmen started an official three-day visit to Montenegro on Sunday. They are discussing the implementation of US-backed development projects and the possible launching of new ones. (Beta - 10/08/03; Tanjug - 09/08/03)
